comment.body:
It looks like you only want the direct messages. If that's the case, use `ig.realtime.on('message', fn)`. Where with `fn`, you can do something like this:

```js
ig.realtime.on('message', ({message: data}) => {
  switch (data.op) { /* ... */ }
});
```

See [`MessageSyncMessageWrapper`](https://github.com/Nerixyz/instagram_mqtt/blob/master/src/realtime/messages/message-sync.message.ts#L4-L6) and [`MessageSyncMessage`](https://github.com/Nerixyz/instagram_mqtt/blob/master/src/realtime/messages/message-sync.message.ts#L47-L83).

